Some of my Ubuntu systems get a 

deb-src http://http.us.debian.org/debian/ unstable main non-free contrib

in /etc/apt/sources.list which is _harmless_ : as it points to sources, it
will never install binaries that could break.  But you _can_ get access to
sources before the corresponding packages come to you via bi-annual Ubuntu
updates.  As discussed here -- so then

	  apt-get update
	  apt-get source -b jags

would build jags. (I do the build in a chroot but it is otherwise the same).

